# LeakFixer Buddy - Environment Variables

## Sandbox (master branch)

```env
# SQLite database (local development)
DATABASE_URL="file:./db/custom.db"

# Demo mode (mock Telegram auth)
DEMO_MODE="true"
```

## Production (main branch - Vercel)

```env
# Supabase PostgreSQL - Connection Pooling (for app)
# Port 6543 - use this for DATABASE_URL
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"

# Supabase PostgreSQL - Direct Connection (for migrations)
# Port 5432 - use this for DIRECT_DATABASE_URL
DIRECT_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres"

# Telegram Bot Token (from @BotFather)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN="123456789:ABCdefGHIjklMNOpqrsTUVwxyz"
```

## How to get Supabase URLs

1. Go to Supabase Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Database
2. Find "Connection string" section
3. Copy **Connection pooling** URL (port 6543) → `DATABASE_URL`
4. Copy **Direct connection** URL (port 5432) → `DIRECT_DATABASE_URL`
5. Replace `[YOUR-PASSWORD]` with your database password

## Notes

- `DATABASE_URL` uses port 6543 (pgbouncer) for better performance
- `DIRECT_DATABASE_URL` uses port 5432 for migrations
- Both URLs use the same password
